  "doc_id": "1661",
  "text": "Mania-like behavior was induced by single i.c.v. injection of 5 lL of 1 mmol/L ouabain (Sigma, St. Louis, MO) dissolved in artificial cerebrospinal fluid (aCSF) 4 days after the cannulation surgery. The aCSF consisted of 124 mmol/L NaCl, 5 mmol/L KCl, 3.7 mmol/L MgSO 4 , 23 mmol/L NaHCO 3 , and 0.75 mmol/L NaH 2 PO 4 , pH 7.4 [CITATION_1] ). Open field activity was examined immediately after i.c.v. injection of ouabain and also at 7 days post injection.",
